#Text=William Finch ( merchant )
#Text=William Finch ( died 1613 ) was an English merchant in the service of the East India Company ( EIC ) .
#Text=He travelled to India along with Captain Hawkins during the reign of the Mughal emperor Jehangir .
#Text=The two of them attended on the emperor at the Mughal court and established trade relations between England and India .
#Text=Finch subsequently explored various cities in India and left a valuable account of them in his journal , which was subsequently published .
#Text=Career
#Text=Finch was a native of London .
#Text=He was agent to an expedition sent by the East India Company , under Captains Hawkins and Keeling , in 1607 to treat with the Great Mogul .
#Text=Hawkins and Finch landed at Surat on 24 August 1608 .
#Text=They were violently opposed by the Portuguese .
#Text=Finch , however , obtained permission from the governor of Cambay to dispose of the goods in their vessels .
#Text=Incited by the Portuguese , who seized two of the English ships , the natives refused to have dealings with the company 's representatives .
#Text=During these squabbles Finch fell ill , and Hawkins , proceeding to Agra alone , obtained favourable notice from the Emperor Jehangir .
#Text=Finch recovered , and joined Hawkins at Agra on 14 April 1610 .
#Text=The two remained at the mogul 's court for about a year and a half .
#Text=Finch refused tempting offers to attach himself permanently to the service of Jehangir .
#Text=Hawkins returned to England , but Finch delayed his departure in order to make further explorations , visiting Byana and Lahore among other places .
#Text=Finch made careful observations on the commerce and natural products of the districts visited .
#Text=In 1612 the Moghul emperor confirmed and extended the privileges he had promised to Finch and Hawkins , and the East India Company in that year set up their first little factory at Surat .
#Text=Exploration
#Text=Finch explored various cities in India , including Delhi , Ambala , Sultanpur , Ayodhya and Lahore , and left valuable accounts of these places in his diary .
#Text=He intended to return to Europe overland , but died en route in Baghdad in 1612 probably due to infected water .
#Text=His belongings were saved and returned to the East India Company .
#Text=Reverend Samuel Purchas found Finch 's journal in the archives of the Company and published an abridged version of it as a chapter in his " Pilgrimes " . [ 1 ]
#Text=In Ayodhya , Finch was an early witness to the location of the Ram Janmabhoomi ( the birth place of Rama ) , the source of the present day Ayodhya dispute .
#Text=Finch did not mention the birthplace or a mosque ( Babri Masjid , believed to have been constructed by a general of Babur ) .
#Text=He did mention ruins , which were apparently believed to be Rama 's castle and houses .
#Text=Scholar Hans T. Bakker , who made a detailed study of Ayodhya , takes Finch 's account to be an authentic record of the state of the Ramkot area at that time . [ 2 ] [ 3 ]
